ğŸ‘ŒKey Insights
ğŸ‡Cars account for the majority of casualties (80%), followed by buses and vans.
ğŸ‡Fatal casualties are significantly lower compared to serious and slight injuries.
ğŸ‡Dry road surfaces have the highest number of casualties, while icy roads have the least.
ğŸ‡Urban areas contribute to a larger share of accidents, but rural areas also have a significant impact.

